The paper presents a prototype of a semantic wiki that uses a controlled natural language (Attempto Controlled English) for representing its content. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), and software engineering (cs.SE). However, given the focus on semantic web technologies and knowledge representation, cs.AI and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories.
